## Setup

Create a virtual environment:

    python -m venv .venv

Activate it on Windows PowerShell:

    .venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

Activate it on Mac/Linux:

    source .venv/bin/activate

Install dependencies:

    pip install -r requirements.txt

## Run the App

    python app.py

Open the app in a browser:

    http://127.0.0.1:5000

Difficulty can be selected with query strings:

    http://127.0.0.1:5000/?difficulty=easy
    http://127.0.0.1:5000/?difficulty=medium
    http://127.0.0.1:5000/?difficulty=hard

## Gameplay Notes

- Select a cell and choose a number from the number pad.
- Correct entries are validated against the generated solution.
- Wrong entries are shown visually.
- Notes mode allows pencil marks without increasing the move count.
- The timer starts on the first number entry or note entry.
- Pause mode stops the timer and hides the board.
- Light/dark mode is saved in local storage.
- The puzzle is complete when all cells match the generated solution.

## Why This Project Exists

This project was built to explore and prove Sudoku generation, validation, and gameplay logic in Python before carrying the idea into a more polished web-game environment.

The Python version is intentionally a prototype/reference build. It is not currently intended to become the final mobile or production version. Future work will likely happen in a JavaScript version designed specifically for EddiesGames.xyz or a similar browser-game platform.

